132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 541
H.P. 360 House of Representatives, February 11, 2025
An Act to Promote Awareness of the Maine Parentage Act
Reference to the Committee on Health and Human Services suggested and ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative BRIDGEO of Augusta. (BY REQUEST)
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 22 MRSA §2770 is enacted to read:
3 §2770. Maine Parentage Act brochure distribution
4 The Maine Center for Disease Control and Prevention shall create and distribute an
5 informational brochure answering basic questions regarding the Maine Parentage Act. The
6 brochure must be distributed to appropriate public health and medical facilities, physicians'
7 offices and other venues in the State frequented by the general public as determined by the
8 Director of the Maine Center for Disease Control and Prevention.
9 SUMMARY
1100 This bill requires the Department of Health and Human Services, Maine Center for
1111 Disease Control and Prevention to create an informational brochure answering basic
1122 questions regarding the Maine Parentage Act and to distribute the brochure to appropriate
1133 public health and medical facilities, physicians' offices and other venues in the State
1144 frequented by the general public.
